

   The process of rendering of POV-Ray scene is implemented with makefile

 It is convenient, since there are several stages of rendering:
     - convertion of quaternion
     - defining the scene
     - rendering itself

 While working, the correction at any step can be made.
 Therefore makefile is useful in determining what to update and what stage to skip 
 (if changes do not affect them). 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   src: lmp2pov.c  head.pov  RES.ini

  Initial flow of steps:
    1. compile <lmp2pov.c>
    2. run lmp2pov (generates out.pov)
    3. add <head.pov> with scene description
    4. render povray using <RES.ini> 
  clean all:
   rm lmp2pov out.pov scene.pov scene.pov.tga scene.pov.png/jpg/...

